JOB POURPOSE
The SPA Doctor is responsible for aesthetic clinic and non-surgical rejuvenating cosmetic procedures and products. Will advise and provide a tailored-made service for our guests, providing and achieving natural and refreshed looks. Works along with the SPA team, ensuring to provide an integral treatment and developing the highest quality level of guest satisfaction and revenue.
KEY RESPONSIBILITIES
Ensures safe and high-quality guests care in line with MSC Cruises values and policies; ; Conducts patient consultations whereby effectively informing and educating guests about specific aesthetic concerns;; Provides friendly and effective post-treatment follow up where necessary, ensuring the desired results;; Promotes the selling of medical aesthetic products and treatments, delivering outstanding guests service;; Maintains complete and accurate medical records as per MSC Cruises policies;; Ensures constant machinery and stock supervision, according to the Company policies and procedures.; 
JOB REQUIREMENTS
An internationally recognized university Diploma in Medical General practice;; A valid license practice registration;; At least 3 years of post-graduate experience in General Practice;; At least 1 year of proved hands-on solid practice as a Cruise SPA Doctor;; Basic Life support (BLS) certificate;; MSc in Aesthetics and Anti-aging is an advantage;; Proficient speaking, reading, and writing skills in English, a fluent level in 1 or more of the following languages: German, Italian, French, Spanish, Portuguese, Japanese, Russian, Chinese, is a plus;&amp;bull;Strong communication skills;&amp;bull;Ability to work well under pressure;; 
VISA REQUIREMENTS
Possess a valid passport and when possible a seaman book copy.;

